U.S. Bank, one of the country’s largest banks with a history dating to 1863, offers banking products to customers nationwide.﻿﻿ The company has two, unsecured, fixed-rate personal loans for existing U.S. Bank customers with good credit scores.﻿﻿ In this review we will focus on the U.S. Bank Personal Loan, as well as cover a few key details of the U.S. Bank Simple Loan. Find out what you need to know before applying for a U.S. Bank personal loan.  
 Competitive APR Co-Applicants Allowed Quick Access to Funds Discount for Autopay U.S. Bank Account Required No Prequalification Some In-Person Loan Closings Prepayment Penalty 
U.S. Bank offers four personal loan products:﻿﻿
 
Same-day funding may be possible if you meet these two requirements:
 
Otherwise, you can expect to receive the funds by the end of the next business day.
 
Before you begin, it’s important to know that U.S. Bank doesn’t allow you to prequalify with a soft pull on your credit. When you submit an application, there will be a hard inquiry on your credit, which will temporarily lower your score.
 
1. Start the application process by logging into your U.S. Bank account. The company may have already filled in some of the fields, which you will have the option to change. 
 
2. The application will ask for housing details:
 
3. U.S. Bank also wants to know about your job:
 
4. The company will ask about your income. U.S. Bank allows you to include these sources: 
 
The company also allows you to include your spouse’s or domestic partner’s income.
 
5. The next step asks how much you want to borrow, your preferred loan term, and the purpose of the loan. 
 
6. You will have the opportunity to review your application and make changes.
 
7. Before submitting the application, you will review the loan details, including the APR, terms, and information about automatic payments. You will also review and accept the company’s disclosures, credit authorization, and consumer pricing information.
 
8. U.S. Bank will let you know about your loan approval status in less than a minute. It may be possible to close online, but some customers will have to visit a U.S. Bank branch.
 
9. You will have access to the funds within one business day of the loan closing.﻿﻿ 
 
It’s possible to refinance with U.S. Bank if your creditworthiness improves and you want to secure a better APR.
 The U.S. Bank Personal Loan is a solid option for its current customers who have a good credit score. The company offers competitive APRs and fees—with the exception of its prepayment penalty. The U.S. Bank Simple Loan may be worth considering for a one-time emergency, especially in lieu of a payday loan, but it won’t be the cheapest option. Remember, there is no prequalification option so your credit score may be affected as you're comparing rates from multiple lenders. 
